tip.text: Small on space but big on taste! Excellent clubman sandwiches. Closest street parking is at Spottiswoode. No wifi.

formattedAddress: De La Salle University - Dasmariñas, DBB-B, Dasmariñas City, Cavite

tip.text: Walk from one end to the other of this series of interconnected eateries -- interesting things to see. Wifi info conveniently provided on tables but inconveniently not available when I was there.
For what you might spend here, you could get a much better meal down the road at Daily Dose on Jalan Muntri.
Interesting nook at a new mall. Love the old school metal plates and bowls they use. Friendly & chatty staff. Avoid sitting near the door leading to the mall if you don't like the cold.
Easy access from City Hall MRT (head towards the St Andrew's Cathdral exit). Nice loos!
It rained HEAVILY about an hour before we checked out. We were on the top floor (room 605) & this part of the ceiling started to leak. Used a bin to catch the water.
The most interesting place at the basement of Siglap Centre. Got wasted on the Get Wasted tart. Yummy!

tip.text: Had a half-n-half pizza with wagyu beef. The seasoning on the beef was too sweet, made it taste cheap. Excellent otak toast came with huge slabs of otak & french loaf slices.
If you do not want the noise from the bar in the main building, request for a room in the wing across the road.
Hotel provides a wifi code for ALL your devices. It also provides a Samsung smartphone with a free 3G connection for use anywhere.
If you take the MRT, disembark at Raffles station. Take exit J & head for 1 Raffles Quay. Walk through UBS Bank building to Citibank at Asia Square Tower 1. Register with ID at general counter.
You can count on background music sans Bieber. So this place will be a wee bit different with its offerings. Depends if you like different.
Card model of the famous bridge.
Opinions on this place aren't black and white. Only photos are.

tip.text: Don't expect to find any parking space in Everton Park. Head for the multistory lots next door.
The Bricks Family Restaurant gets crowded during breakfast at peak vacation periods. Either eat early or late. Alternatively, ask for a seat outdoors to avoid the noise.
Nice decor inside, but can get noisy when crowded. Sit outside to watch the Legoland world go by.
